  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Cook/Cook",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare and cook meals and tea breaks for residents according to the kitchen menu and food safety standards.</li><li>Assist in menu planning and develop simple and creative recipes.</li><li>Support dietitian during monthly kitchen visits.</li><li>Prepare requisition for store to replenish items for central kitchen.</li><li>Prepare requisitions, kitchen order lists, and estimate food & beverage consumption.</li><li>Receive and verify suppliers’ deliveries and manage inventory to minimise waste and control costs.</li><li>Maintain cleanliness, hygiene and safety in the kitchen, ensure equipment and environment are in compliance with MOH and food hygiene requirements.</li><li>Report any abnormalities of kitchen equipment to the Maintenance Team for rectification and repair.</li><li>Ensure all food and beverages are prepared in-accordance to food safety and hygiene procedures at\nall times.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc tasks assigned by direct report.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum PSLE / PMR qualification or equivalent.</li><li>At least 2-5 years of relevant working experience (central kitchen or economical rice) would be an advantage.</li><li>Preferably with cooking experience in Halal, Chinese, Indian and/or Western cuisine.</li><li>Comfortable with shift work and 6-day work week (7:00am – 3:30pm / 9:00am – 5:30pm).</li><li>Able to read and understand simple English.</li><li>Team player with a positive, people-oriented attitude.</li><li>Physically fit and able to handle transportation of loads and kitchen equipment as required.</li></ul>",
